<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Straight1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Straight</orth> (cf. <emph>Strait</emph>) adj. passing from one point to another by the nearest way, right, direct, not crooked: <cit><quote>s. legs and passing strong,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 297" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 297</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I may be s, though they themselves be bevel,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 121.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 121, 11</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. shr 2.256" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 256</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 2.3.148" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. II, 3, 148</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.1.82" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 1, 82</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.164" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 164</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 5.2.168" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 V, 2, 168</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.1.19" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 1, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.1.38" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 1, 38</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 5.1.110" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V, 1, 110</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>